<promed@promedmail.org>
[This additional case in the north of the country and the 2 preceding
cases in the south have not been confirmed so far by the WHO. As of
27 Jul 2005, the WHO list of laboratory-confirmed human cases of H5N1
avian influenza infection in East Asia since 16 Dec 2004
<http://www.who.int/csr/disease/avian_influenza/country/cases_table_2005_07
_27/en/index.html>
remains at 60 cases and 18 deaths in Viet Nam, 4 cases and 4 deaths
in Cambodia, one case and one death in Indonesia, and none in
Thailand. - Mod.CP]
